## 1. Problem Statement

### The Challenge

Car project owners lack a unified, user-friendly system to document their work. Currently they rely on:

- Scattered spreadsheets and text files (hard to organize and search)
- Unreliable memory and hand-written notes (prone to loss and gaps)
- Photo collections without context or metadata (difficult to retrieve and understand)
- Fragmented online forums and social media (poor searchability, inconsistent format)
- Manual entry into ChatGPT or other AI tools (requires extra steps and subscriptions)

### Pain Points

- **Time-consuming documentation**: Project owners spend hours cataloging work, parts, and costs
- **Information loss**: Critical details about part sourcing, costs, and timelines are forgotten
- **Lack of searchability**: Finding past decisions or maintenance records is frustrating
- **Difficulty sharing progress**: Creating blog posts or shareable updates requires manual effort
- **Fragmented advice**: Best practices are scattered across forums, YouTube, and Reddit
- **Barrier to entry for AI tools**: Non-technical users hesitate to adopt ChatGPT; it requires extra steps and costs

