## 4. Product Definition & Core Features

### User Personas

#### Persona 1: The Weekend Warrior
- Does routine maintenance (oil changes, brakes, fluids)
- Changes spark plugs, filters, minor upgrades
- Wants to track what they've done for resale value or warranty
- Not very technical, doesn't use spreadsheets
- Time-pressed; wants quick entry method
- **Goal**: Know what's been done and when

#### Persona 2: The Enthusiast Builder
- Modifying or upgrading a car (suspension, exhaust, turbo, wheels)
- Takes detailed photos, keeps receipts
- Active on forums, watches YouTube tutorials
- Comfortable with technology
- May want to share progress with friends or online
- **Goal**: Track all work, parts, and decisions; maybe share build progress

#### Persona 3: The Restorer
- Doing a frame-off or major restoration (years-long project)
- Needs detailed inventory of thousands of parts
- Budgeting critical; needs cost breakdowns
- May employ help or collaborate with others
- Wants a historical record of all work done
- **Goal**: Complete organizational system for complex, multi-year projects

#### Persona 4: The Content Creator
- Documenting builds for YouTube, Instagram, TikTok
- Wants to share progress and reach an audience
- Interested in community interaction and feedback
- Might monetize through sponsorships or patreon
- **Goal**: Easy way to publish, build audience, engage community

### Core Feature Set (MVP)

#### Phase 1: Project Basics & Voice Logging
- Create and manage multiple vehicle projects
- Voice-to-text log entry (with manual option)
- Photo/video attachment to log entries
- Basic project information (vehicle specs, location, goals)
- Simple parts list with cost tracking
- Search/browse past logs

#### Phase 2: AI Assistant & Intelligent Organization
- Chat interface with context awareness
- Auto-extraction of parts, costs, time from logs
- Parts recommendation and research
- Maintenance schedule suggestions
- Question answering about the user's specific project

#### Phase 3: Community & Publishing
- Build log publishing (manual or AI-generated)
- Garage subscription (follow other users)
- Upvote/downvote, comments
- Video auto-generation from photos
- Integration with social media sharing

### Feature Roadmap (Post-MVP)

- **Collaborative projects**: Multiple users working on same vehicle
- **Part marketplace integration**: Direct links to suppliers (eBay, Amazon, specialty vendors)
- **Cost analytics & budget planning**: Forecast total project cost
- **Augmented reality**: Visualize parts before purchase
- **Export to PDF**: Generate professional build logs for resale or documentation
- **Mobile-first offline mode**: Access/update logs without internet
- **Integration with mechanic shops**: Share history with trusted repair providers
- **Marketplace for builds/services**: Users can offer restoration services or sell completed projects

