## 6. Technical Architecture (High-Level)

### Platform Stack

**Frontend**
- React Native (iOS/Android) for mobile-first experience
- Optional web dashboard (React)
- Voice recording & transcription UI

**Backend**
- Node.js or Python (FastAPI) REST API
- PostgreSQL for structured data
- S3 or similar for photos/videos
- Vector database for semantic search and AI context

**AI/ML**
- Claude API (via Anthropic) for primary AI features
- Fallback to OpenAI API as option
- Fine-tuning on community data (long-term)
- Voice transcription (Whisper API or similar)
- Video editing automation (FFmpeg library)

**Infrastructure**
- Cloud hosting (AWS, GCP, or Azure)
- CDN for media delivery
- Real-time database for collaborative features (future)

### Key Technical Decisions

1. **Voice transcription**: Use Whisper (OpenAI) or similar—handles accents, noise well
2. **AI model**: Primary Claude (Anthropic), secondary OpenAI for cost/redundancy
3. **Mobile-first**: Build native mobile experience first; web admin/dashboard second
4. **Offline-first**: Local storage on device, sync when online
5. **Privacy by default**: Project data encrypted; community data explicitly shared

### Data Model (Core Entities)
```
User
├── Garage (collection of projects)
    ├── Vehicle (individual car/project)
    │   ├── Project Details (specs, goals, status)
    │   ├── Log Entries (voice/manual, dated)
    │   │   ├── Photos/Videos
    │   │   └── Extracted Metadata (parts, costs, time)
    │   ├── Parts Inventory
    │   ├── Maintenance Schedule
    │   └── Resources (tools, links, documents)
    └── Build Posts (published content)
        ├── Generated from logs
        ├── Photos, videos, narrative
        └── Community engagement (likes, comments)
```

